mapping process¶

In [21]:
group_sub1 = df_sub1.groupby(by = 'Class')
group_sub1_kmeans = df_sub1.groupby(by = 'kmeans')

fig = plt.figure()
ax_sub_origin = plt.axes(projection = '3d')
for (ele_id,ele) in group_sub1:
  ax_sub_origin.scatter3D(ele['X1'], ele['X2'],ele['X3'],label = ele_id)
plt.legend()


fig2 = plt.figure()
ax_sub_clustering = plt.axes(projection = '3d')
for (ele_id,ele) in group_sub1_kmeans:
  ax_sub_clustering.scatter(ele['X1'], ele['X2'], ele['X3'],label = ele_id)
plt.legend()

plt.show()

Data visualization process¶

In [50]:
group_sub1 = df_sub1.groupby(by = 'Class')
group_sub1_kmeans = df_sub1.groupby(by = 'kmeans_relabel')

fig = plt.figure()
ax_sub_origin = plt.axes(projection = '3d')
for (ele_id,ele) in group_sub1:
  ax_sub_origin.scatter3D(ele['X1'], ele['X2'],ele['X3'],label = ele_id)
ax_sub_origin.set(title = 'Visualiztion of origin')
ax_sub_origin.set_xlabel('X1')
ax_sub_origin.set_ylabel('X2')
ax_sub_origin.set_zlabel('X3')
plt.legend()

fig2 = plt.figure()
ax_sub_clustering = plt.axes(projection = '3d')
for (ele_id,ele) in group_sub1_kmeans:
  ax_sub_clustering.scatter(ele['X1'], ele['X2'], ele['X3'],label = ele_id)
ax_sub_clustering.set(title = 'Visualiztion of clustering')
ax_sub_clustering.set_xlabel('X1')
ax_sub_clustering.set_ylabel('X2')
ax_sub_clustering.set_zlabel('X3')
plt.legend()

plt.show()

hierarchical¶

clustering process¶

The output label of agglomerative Clustering changed every time you run the code. Please don't run this cell again

In [39]:
agglomer = AgglomerativeClustering(n_clusters = 7)
agglomer.fit(df_sub1.iloc[:,:-1])
df_sub1['agglomer'] = kmeans_model1.labels_

df_sub6['agglomer'] = agglomer_model6.labels_

The accuracy must be less than 100% if using external validation.¶

It is meaningless to do external validation, which means 'no cluster'(also called n_cluster equal 1).¶

kmeans¶

If we do clustering, metrics decreases. we'd better make no cluster.

In [82]:
kmeans_model8 = KMeans(n_clusters = 1, random_state = 2170)
kmeans_model8.fit(df_sub8.iloc[:,:-1])
df_sub8['kmeans=1'] = pd.Series(kmeans_model8.labels_).map({0:1})
kmeans_model8 = KMeans(n_clusters = 2, random_state = 2171)
kmeans_model8.fit(df_sub8.iloc[:,:-1])
df_sub8['kmeans=2'] = pd.Series(kmeans_model8.labels_).map({0:1,1:2})
kmeans_model8 = KMeans(n_clusters = 3, random_state = 2172)
kmeans_model8.fit(df_sub8.iloc[:,:-1])
df_sub8['kmeans=3'] = pd.Series(kmeans_model8.labels_).map({0:1,1:2,2:3})

metrics_f1 = []
metrics_accuracy = []
for i in ['kmeans='+str(i) for i in range(1,4)]:
  metrics_f1.append(metrics.f1_score(df_sub8['Class'],df_sub8[i], average = 'weighted'))
  metrics_accuracy.append(metrics.accuracy_score(df_sub8['Class'],df_sub8[i]))

plt.plot(range(1,4),metrics_f1,label = 'f1_score')
plt.plot(range(1,4),metrics_accuracy,label = 'accuracy')
plt.legend()
plt.title('Why there should be no cluster in data 8 based on external validation metrics')
plt.show()

agglomer¶

we'd better make no cluster.

In [80]:
agglomer_model8 = AgglomerativeClustering(n_clusters = 1)
agglomer_model8.fit(df_sub8.iloc[:,:-1])
df_sub8['agglomer=1'] = pd.Series(agglomer_model8.labels_).map({0:1})
agglomer_model8 = AgglomerativeClustering(n_clusters = 2)
agglomer_model8.fit(df_sub8.iloc[:,:-1])
df_sub8['agglomer=2'] = pd.Series(agglomer_model8.labels_).map({0:1,1:2})
agglomer_model8 = AgglomerativeClustering(n_clusters = 3)
agglomer_model8.fit(df_sub8.iloc[:,:-1])
df_sub8['agglomer=3'] = pd.Series(agglomer_model8.labels_).map({0:1,1:2,2:3})

metrics_f1 = []
metrics_accuracy = []
for i in ['agglomer='+str(i) for i in range(1,4)]:
  metrics_f1.append(metrics.f1_score(df_sub8['Class'],df_sub8[i], average = 'weighted'))
  metrics_accuracy.append(metrics.accuracy_score(df_sub8['Class'],df_sub8[i]))

plt.plot(range(1,4),metrics_f1,label = 'f1_score')
plt.plot(range(1,4),metrics_accuracy,label = 'accuracy')
plt.legend()
plt.title('Why there should be no cluster in data 8 based on external validation metrics')
plt.show()
